article.headline: Pullian scores 22 as Milwaukee knocks off Duquesne 80-74
article.description: — Kentrell Pullian's 22 points helped Milwaukee defeat Duquesne 80-74 on Tuesday night.
article.linkText: Pullian scores 22 as Milwaukee knocks off Duquesne 80-74
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — Kentrell Pullian's 22 points helped Milwaukee defeat Duquesne 80-74 on Tuesday night. Pullian added seven rebounds and four steals for the Panthers (2-2). Themus Fulks scored 15 points while going 4 of 8 and 7 of 10 from the free-throw line. AJ McKee shot 6 for 15, including 2 for 9 from beyond the arc to finish with 15 points. Jake DiMichele finished with 21 points and two steals for the Dukes (0-4). Tre Dinkins added 20 points and four assists for Duquesne. Milwaukee went into halftime leading Duquesne 37-28. Pullian scored 12 points in the half. Milwaukee used a 10-0 run in the second half to build a 12-point lead at 68-56. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
